🔴 ISSUE #001 | CRITICAL BUG
Type: Runtime Crash
Difficulty: ⭐⭐⭐
Assigned To: Unassigned

🐛 The Problem
The lexer crashes immediately when it encounters an empty input file. No error message, just a segmentation fault.

💡 The Fix
Add a null-check at the very beginning of the tokenize() function.
python
# BEFORE
def tokenize(source):
    return process(source)  # Boom if source is empty

# AFTER
def tokenize(source):
    if not source or len(source.strip()) == 0:
        return []  # Graceful empty token list
    return process(source)
